The progress of all eight provinces is on track.

UNICEF and partners have achieved important results in improving immunization and health services, conducting a first health system evaluation and the effective implementation of the prevention of mother-to-child HIV transmission.

Effective supply X logistics support to programme delivery and office functioning and improvement in overall efficiency in supply X logistics management. Emergency response was dominant Durant the reported period. Constructions, rehabilitations, latrines funded by GPE and UE have been finalized.

Advances were made within all health sectors, where UNICEF remains a crucial partner to the Government. The focus was mainly on building capacity and supporting all routine health activities with supervision, acquisition of materials, promotion of best practices and technical support. Lack of funds has impeded more results.

UNICEF increased the employability of 28,739 (42.7% Male; 57.3% Female) youth through access to BLN, TVET, skills training and innovation courses, and increased its support to youth to help with the transition of learning to earning through employment support services and more income generating activities.
